CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 21, 1941, pg. 4, reads: "The popular Shedrick Fields of Webster avenue flew to the flight. 'Joe came through like a real champ... and a gentleman,' he said. He is pictured here as he boarded him plane in Pittsburgh. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Shedrick Fields wearing eyeglasses and standing on steps of TWA airplane
